verbose_text: The grouping of mutations into functional categories is as follows : class I, no synthesis of CFTR; class II, degradation of CFTR in the endoplasmic reticulum; class III, transport of CFTR to the cell membrane, but no appropriate response; class IV, diminished action of CFTR in the cell membrane; and class V, normal but inadequate amounts of CFTR.
evidence: transport of CFTR to the cell membrane
